We already have [`System.Threading.Timeout.InfiniteTimeSpan`](https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/blob/master/src/Common/src/CoreLib/System/Threading/Timeout.cs#L12), which uses `-1` for milliseconds.

@KrzysztofCwalina proposed to add an alias under `TimeSpan` which would more discoverable:

> I think it would be useful. The Timeout type is in Threading namespace and we don’t want to use it as timing out has nothing to do with threading.

### Proposed API

```C#
namespace System
{
    public struct TimeSpan : IComparable
    {
        public static readonly TimeSpan MinValue;
    }
}
```

